The paper deals with coding theory over a finite commutative non-chain ring, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on polyadic constacyclic codes, which are a type of cyclic code (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the Gray images of polyadic negacyclic codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions self-dual, isodual, self-orthogonal, and complementary dual codes, which are topics in algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses \(\alpha \)-constacyclic codes, which are a generalization of cyclic codes (cs.SI).
